item.title: Privacy Policy
item.dc:creator: tns_admin
item.content:encoded:
Trans Neptune Spaceway is committed to protecting your Personal Information that you share with us. We want you to understand our Privacy Policy and what it means to you, our customer, so please take a moment to review this Privacy Policy (referred to as Policy). By using our website or the services offered by us, you are consenting to our use of such personal information as you provide to us as described herein. If you do not consent to our use of your information, please do not use our services. Any questions you have about our Privacy Policy, or the information contained herein can be directed to our Privacy Officer at: privacyofficer@TNS.com

We need to collect, use and disclose personal information in order to perform our business functions and activities, including making and managing travel bookings on behalf of our customers. We are firmly committed to protecting the privacy and confidentiality of personal information with various physical, electronic and procedural safeguards. For the purposes of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) we assume a role of either the data processor or data controller for any personal information you provide to us in connection with our relationship. The exact role assumed depends on the context of our relationship with you and the purpose of the processing of personal information.

For the provision of retail travel services by Travel Talk, we will be the data controller and this Policy shall apply. Likewise, for the purpose of all our marketing activities, we will be the data controller and this Policy shall apply. By providing personal information to us, you agree that this Policy will apply to how we handle your personal information and you consent to us collecting, using and disclosing your personal information as detailed in this Policy. If you do not agree with any part of this Policy, you must not provide your personal information to us.

If you do not provide us with your personal information, or if you withdraw a consent that you have given under this Policy, this may affect our ability to provide services to you or negatively impact the services we can provide to you.

Management personals hold the right to decide upon the amount to be paid as advance payment, based on the plan of the tour & the time left for the commencement of the tour.

Mode of Payment: Overseas advance payment can be made through Wire Transfer to our bank.

Cancellation Policy: In the event of cancellation of tour / travel services due to any avoidable / unavoidable reason/s we must be notified of the same in writing. Cancellation charges will be effective from the date we receive advice in writing, and cancellation charges would be as follows:

  • 45 days prior to arrival: Cost of oxygen, space travel and accommodation is refunded
  • 15 days prior to arrival: Cost of oxygen and accommodation is refunded
  • 07 days prior to arrival: Only cost of oxygen is refunded.
  • 48 hours prior to arrival OR No Show: No Refund

Note: Written cancellation will accept on all working days, except Sunday, Any cancellation sent on Sunday's will be considered on next working day (Monday).

 Safaris cancellation: All the alien life safaris booked into any of Earth like planets are non refundable. Even date change request will be considered as cancellation and no payment will be refunded/ adjusted against it.

item.title: Spaceship and Suit
item.dc:creator: tns_admin
item.content:encoded:
Specifications for SpaceShipTwo

SpaceShipTwo will be 60 feet (18.3 meters) long with a wingspan of 27 feet (8.2 meters) and a tail height of 15 feet (4.6 meters). It's about twice the size of normal SPACESHIP.

The passenger compartment will contain will be 12 feet (3.7 meters) long and 90 inches (228.6 centimeters) wide. We plans to make the cabin area as comfortable as possible. It will be pressurized, allowing the passengers to breathe normally without masks or pressure suits (known as a "short-sleeve environment").
Windows in the passenger compartment will be 13 inches (33 centimeters) wide by 17 inches (43 centimeters) tall. The pilots' windows will be 21 inches (53.3 centimeters) wide. The exact lifting capacity of the carrier craft will depend on the plan , but it will be greater than the weight of normal SpaceShip.This means that it could have the capability to carry larger vehicles or unmanned satellite launching rockets for high-altitude launches.
Carbon fiber panels sandwiched around a honeycomb core will give SpaceShipTwo remarkable strength for its weight. Power is provided by a hybrid rocket which uses neuclear fission process. The liquid is stored under pressure, so no fuel pumps are needed. Overall, hybrid rocket systems are considered among the safest types of rockets.
There will be autopilot and computer control -- the pilots can also directly control everything through mechanical and electric-assist controls. Thrusters in the nose are used to alter pitch and yaw when we will travel small distances, Navigation is handled by a GPS-enabled LCD screen that displays SpaceShipTwo in relation to a simulated space.

Spacesuit

  • Helmet consist of screen visuals and mike 
  • Screen visuals that allows them to know about the creatures if they are harmful or friendly (if its harmful it turns red if not then green) 
  • There will be oxygen tanks at back. Tanks capacity is they can survive for 4 hours with it but also then can refill there tanks in pods which will take 5 mins
  • Thrusters are given at the bottom as well as at the back that will help them to fly or move in mid air 
  • Shoulder pads helps them with flight stabilizer
  • On hand there are navigator screen
  • On Forearm there will be tabs that will help them to adjust there suits according to the climate and if they want to convey any message it can be conveyed through tab

item.title: Explore Planets
item.dc:creator: tns_admin
item.content:encoded:
Destinations:

  • View of Kepler Planet: With the advantage of travelling to different solar systems, we are going the explore the nearest ones first, the Kepler series. More than hundreds of suns and thousands of planets which lie 150 light years away are ready to get explored. Some of the most breathtaking views of all differently coloured planets seen together will be a rather new scene to behold.
  • Triton: Neptunes largest moon, which is made of only and only ice. A totally new experience of Ice skating and skiing is awaiting on the moon.
  • Panthalassic: The first aqua planet discovered by NASA. Great mysteries lie inside the aquatic surface of the planet, which will be discovered by you. With gravity and atmosphere different than that of earth, an innovative water park has been constructed with the most amusing water rides ever. Keep your eyes sharp, as any new species found will be your discovery and will be known by your name.
  • Vesta: It is a giant crystalline body, with all type of colourful and eccentric shaped crystals you may have never seen. Most of the rocks change colours at different times in the day, and some are floating pieces denying the laws of gravity. Explore the crystal caves and Mirror mazes inside them, and collect as many crystals as you want. You get to take some of them home too.
  • Haumea: Found in Cupier Belt, the dwarf planet has the rotation time of 4 hours. An entire day with cloudless skies full of stars and other planets visible from its surface could be a rest trip for the explorers. Best place to visit for the stargazers and daydreamers.
  • Psamathe: Neptunes other moon, a gas body with the gravity of 0.003 m/s2. Getting into the atmosphere of the moon means a jump directly into the space. Enjoy your most eccentric bungee jumping experience over here
  • Planet E2: With atmosphere and gravity similar to that of earth, the planet has the lifestyle quite different from that of earth. Fauna not as communicative as us and flora is not necessarily herbivore. Adventurous trek awaits at every location of this planet. Only rule is survive and explore.
  • Neptune: Our last planet of the solar system and the blue gas giant is also going to be our stoppage. Diving and floating inside the gaseous surface will surely be fun and a different experience than water diving. It is also going to be our fuel refueling stop.
  • Black Hole: Get ready to go beyond time and mass. We are now going to enter the black hole and enter into a new galaxy , or a new dimension, or a new universe. Whats is going to happen?? We need to check. We need to explore.
  • Nebula: With our advanced communication satellites we are now able to track any dying star near or far away. The view is not something to be missed. Grab your popcorn wear your glasses and lets see the explosion, and the beautiful nebula that follows.

item.title: Privacy Policy
item.dc:creator: tns_admin
item.content:encoded:
Who we are

Our website address is: http://localhost/tns.

What personal data we collect and why we collect it

Comments

When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor’s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.

An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.

Media

If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.

Contact forms

Cookies

If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.

If you visit our login page, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.

When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select "Remember Me", your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.

If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.

Embedded content from other websites

Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.

These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.

Analytics

Who we share your data with

How long we retain your data

If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.

For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.

What rights you have over your data

If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.

Where we send your data

Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.

Your contact information

Additional information

How we protect your data

What data breach procedures we have in place

What third parties we receive data from

What automated decision making and/or profiling we do with user data

item.title: Training Program
item.dc:creator: tns_admin
item.content:encoded:
It is just a criteria before travelling so their body gets comfortable and adaptive to the spacesuit and the environment.Its our effort to give them a head-start so that they dont feel uncomfortable and that can give us the idea how each one experiences and about their body adaptivity.

This is split into three main sections. 

First, newcomers  have to pass a two/four/six months course of basic training.The time span depends upon the package they are availing. The candidates learn about space technology and science, basic medical skills, and how the International Space Station (ISS) works. They also become familiar with scuba diving.

They learn about the special tasks linked with their travel and they become familiar with weightlessness doing parabolic flights.

The training will make them spaceship and spacesuit friendly .Which would help them to know exact characteristics and uses of spacesuit features.  

The person training the candidates will be professionally trained themselves.
